# Conventional Commits

All commit messages must follow Conventional Commits 1.0.0:

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Types
- `fix:` — patches a bug (PATCH in SemVer)
- `feat:` — introduces a new feature (MINOR in SemVer)
- `BREAKING CHANGE:` — footer or `!` after type for breaking API changes (MAJOR in SemVer)
- `build:` — build system or external dependencies
- `chore:` — maintenance tasks
- `ci:` — CI configuration
- `docs:` — documentation only
- `style:` — formatting, no code change
- `refactor:` — neither fix nor feature
- `perf:` — performance improvement
- `test:` — adding or correcting tests

## Rules
- Type and description are required
- Description must be lowercase, imperative mood, no period at end
- Body must begin one blank line after description
- `BREAKING CHANGE:` in footer or `!` after type/scope signals a breaking change
- Scopes are optional but recommended (e.g., `feat(export):`, `fix(auth):`)

## Examples
```
feat(export): add CSV download for payment configs
fix(auth): handle expired JWT tokens gracefully
docs: update API documentation for v2 endpoints
refactor!: rename PaymentConfig to PaymentRule
```
